This article is a press gaggle by Press Secretary Josh Earnest en route to Detroit, MI, on January 7, 2015. The article covers a range of topics, including the President's response to the terror attacks in Paris, an upcoming announcement about assistance for middle-class homeowners, and the President's visit to Ford's Michigan Assembly Plant. Earnest also addresses questions about the U.S. assessment of the Paris attackers, the U.S. response to the attacks, and the President's views on freedom of the press. Earnest also discusses the President's views on trade agreements and the impact on the auto industry. The article ends with a brief mention of the President's announcement on changes to the Federal Housing Administration.